The 2015_0912 Code Challenge is a learning exercise for students attending this Meetup:

%br/
%br/

%a(href='http://www.meetup.com/Dans-Linux-JavaScript-Class/events/225223500/' target='x')
  http://www.meetup.com/Dans-Linux-JavaScript-Class/events/225223500/

%br/
%br/

%ul
  %li Install Ubuntu 14.04.3 on your laptop
  %li
    Useful:
    %a(href='http://releases.ubuntu.com/14.04/ubuntu-14.04.3-desktop-amd64.iso' target='x')
      http://releases.ubuntu.com/14.04/ubuntu-14.04.3-desktop-amd64.iso

  %li
    Useful:
    %a(href='https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads' target='x')
      https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads

  %li
    Enhance Ubuntu:
    %pre
      =render 'code_challenge2015_09121'

  %li
    Create account named ann:
    %pre
      %code.bash
        useradd ann -m -s /bin/bash
        passwd ann
        ssh -YA ann@localhost

  %li
    Install Node.js in this folder: ~ann/node/
    %br/
    Useful:
    %a(href='https://nodejs.org/dist/v4.0.0/node-v4.0.0-linux-x64.tar.gz' target='x')
      https://nodejs.org/dist/v4.0.0/node-v4.0.0-linux-x64.tar.gz


  %li
    Add Node.js to PATH:
    %pre
      %code.bash export PATH="/home/ann/node/bin:${PATH}"
    
  %li
    Run a test:
    %pre
      %code.bash
        which node
        node -e 'console.log("hello world")'

  %li
    Install CoffeScript to test npm:
    %pre
      %code.bash
        which npm
        npm install -g coffee-script
        ls -la /home/ann/node/lib/node_modules/
        which coffee
        coffee -e 'console.log "hello coffee!"'

  %li
    Start work on an app:
    %pre
      %code.bash
        mkdir ~ann/app10
        cd    ~ann/app10
        echo  node_modules > .gitignore
        npm init # Creates package.json (displayed below)
        npm install --save http-server

  %li
    Add HTML file to app: ~ann/app10/index.html
    %pre
      =render 'code_challenge2015_09123'

  %li
    Test the app:
    %pre
      %code.bash node ~ann/app10/node_modules/http-server/bin/http-server
    visit: 
    %a(href='http://localhost:8080' target='x')
      http://localhost:8080

  %li
    Commit the app to a git repository:
    %pre
      %code.bash
        git init
        git add .
        git commit -am 'hello app10'

%br/
%br/

At this point I should have the app running on Linux on my laptop.

%br/
%br/

I can follow more steps to deploy the app to Heroku:

%ul
  %li
    Enhance ~ann/app10/package.json so it has an "engines" property:
    %pre
      =render 'code_challenge2015_09124'

  %li
    Create a one-line Procfile:
    %pre
      %code.bash echo 'web: node node_modules/http-server/bin/http-server -p $PORT' > Procfile

  %li
    Install Heroku Toolbelt:
    %br/
    %a(href='http://www.google.com/search?q=How+to+install+Heroku+Toolbelt+on+Linux' target='x')
      http://www.google.com/search?q=How+to+install+Heroku+Toolbelt+on+Linux

  %li
    Create Heroku Account (cost: $0.00!):
    %br/
    %a(href='https://www.heroku.com' target='x')
      https://www.heroku.com
    %br/
    Memorize login and password

  %li
    Create Blank Heroku App and then git-push my app in:
    %pre
      %code.bash
        heroku auth:login
        heroku app create x20150910
        git add .
        git commit -am ready4heroku
        git push heroku master
    I should see something like this:
    %pre
      =render 'code_challenge2015_09125'
  %li
    When I visit the page served by the app, I should see something like this:
    %br/
    %img(src='/images/code_challenge2015_09121.png')

